text: Pluck is an unincorporated community in Polk County, Texas, United States. ==History== A variant name was "Stryker." A post office called Stryker was established in 1885, and closed in 1913, and a post office called Pluck was in operation from 1918 until 1951. The origin of the name "Pluck" is obscure. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Polk County, Texas Category:Unincorporated communities in Texas
title: Pluck, Texas
